## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Flask 3.1
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 17 with Flask-SQLAlchemy
- **Migrations**: Flask-Migrate (Alembic)
- **Cache**: Redis 7 with Flask-Caching
- **Package Manager**: uv
- **Testing**: pytest
- **Formatting**: ruff

## Project Structure

- `app/` - Application package (factory pattern)
- `app/__init__.py` - Application factory (`create_app`)
- `app/extensions.py` - Flask extension instances
- `app/blueprints/` - Route handlers organized by blueprint
- `app/models/` - SQLAlchemy ORM models
- `app/templates/` - Jinja2 HTML templates
- `migrations/` - Database migrations (Flask-Migrate)
- `tests/` - Test suite
- `config.py` - Configuration classes (Development, Production, Testing)
- `wsgi.py` - WSGI entry point
- `docs/supporting/` - Supporting documentation

## Development Commands

```bash
make start       # Start Docker Compose stack
make stop        # Stop all services
make bash        # Shell into web container
make shell       # Flask interactive shell
make test        # Run pytest suite
make migrate     # Run database migrations
make migration   # Create new migration (MSG="description")
make lint        # Run ruff linter
make format      # Auto-format with ruff
make reqs        # Compile requirements
```

## Conventions

- Application factory pattern in `app/__init__.py`
- Use UUID primary keys for models exposed in URLs
- Organize routes into blueprints in `app/blueprints/`
- Configuration via classes in `config.py`
- Tests go in `tests/` directory, not next to source files
- Use `ruff` for code formatting
- Use type hints for function signatures
